item.title: 'Yell at me, if ...': Elon Musk responds to Zuckerberg’s regret over Covid-19 censorship
item.description: Elon Musk reiterated the significance of supporting diverse viewpoints on social media after Mark Zuckerberg expressed regret for censoring Covid-19 content under pressure from the Biden administration. This disclosure ignited political debates, with former President Trump using it to bolster his claims regarding the 2020 election.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Duty to warn': Canadian police alert aide to slain Sikh separatist Nijjar of increased threats
item.description: Canadian police have issued a warning to Inderjeet Singh Gosal, an aide to the assassinated Sikh separatist leader Hardeep Singh Nijjar, due to increased threats. Nijjar’s assassination has spurred controversy, with allegations about potential Indian government involvement. Canada’s police have charged four individuals, while India denies any role. The FBI is investigating other related threats.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Is droplets a source of Mpox transmission? What we know so far
item.description: The World Health Organization emphasizes that mpox is chiefly transmitted through close physical contact, rather than respiratory droplets. The Democratic Republic of Congo faces outbreaks involving Clade 1a and Clade 1b variants. Ongoing studies aim to better understand the transmission and severity of the new Clade 1b.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Japan on high alert as Typhoon Shanshan nears with torrential rain and gusty winds
item.description: Japan is bracing for Typhoon Shanshan, expected to bring severe weather, including heavy rain and strong winds. Airlines like ANA and Japan Airlines have cancelled numerous domestic flights, and some bullet trains are suspended. The storm is expected to hit Kyushu island and possibly reach central and eastern areas, including Tokyo. Authorities advise caution.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Nancy Pelosi’s raw response to January 6 riot: 'Trump got to pay a price’, unreleased footage shows
item.description: Unreleased footage from January 7, 2021, portrays former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi condemning Trump post-Capitol riot. Captured by her daughter and shared with the House Committee, it highlights Pelosi’s immediate outrage and her determination to hold Trump accountable. The footage also reveals Pelosi's frustration over security lapses and chaotic evacuation.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Heat advisory and severe storms hit Michigan's Lansing: Over 16,000 without power, weather warnings in effect
item.description: A heat advisory has been issued in Lansing due to a late-summer heatwave, with temperatures in the low 90s and high humidity making it feel like 105 degrees. Severe storms are expected to bring damaging winds, rain, and hail. Power outages affect over 16,100 customers.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: North Korea test-fires rocket launcher with new 'guiding system'
item.description: North Korea's Kim Jong Un supervised a test-firing of a 240mm multiple rocket launcher equipped with a new guiding system. This activity is part of North Korea's broader initiative to strengthen its military capabilities. The US and South Korea have alleged that Pyongyang has been supplying Russia with missiles. Tensions between the Koreas are at a high point.

item.title: Is Elon Musk’s SpaceX reign over? Rocket Lab’s Neutron set to rival Falcon 9 in 2025
item.description: Peter Beck, CEO of Rocket Lab, plans to introduce the Neutron rocket in mid-2025 as a direct competitor to SpaceX's Falcon 9. This new rocket aims to offer partially reusable cargo transportation at a lower cost. Beck's goal is to balance the market and facilitate satellite launches, marking a significant challenge to Elon Musk's SpaceX.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala to break media silence in high-stakes interview, Trump adviser slams her for 'hiding behind Walz'
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris will participate in her first interview since becoming the Democratic nominee, joined by Minnesota Governor Tim Walz. The interview will air on CNN, focusing on policy shifts, Harris's evolving positions, and concerns about Biden's mental health. Harris's media silence has been criticized, with some questioning the decision to tape the interview.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Telegram boss held over probe into child porn, drug trafficking on app
Muizzu says bid to topple govt, cites main bank's curbs on dollar spending
item.description: Authorities in the Maldives are investigating claims that President Mohamed Muizzu has faced attempted destabilization through financial discontent. The Bank of Maldives imposed foreign exchange limits, stirring online criticism and accusations of a plot. Reversing the restrictions, Muizzu suggested some bank directors remain loyal to the previous administration.

item.title: Israeli military rescues hostage, father of 11, from Gaza tunnel in 'complex op'
item.description: Israel rescued Qaid Farhan Alkadi, an Arab Bedouin minority member, from an underground tunnel in Gaza. Alkadi, kidnapped during the October 7 Hamas attack, was held for 326 days. The rescue offers hope but reminds Israel of others still in captivity. Prime Minister Netanyahu emphasized ongoing military pressure and negotiations to free remaining hostages.

item.title: F-16s dent Russia's strike on Ukraine
item.description: Russia continued missile and drone attacks on Ukraine, killing at least six. President Zelensky confirmed Western-supplied F-16s intercepted some missiles. He called for more defense support following extensive strikes on Ukrainian infrastructure. Kyiv's air defenses reportedly neutralized all threats aimed at the city. The attacks appear to be in retaliation for Ukraine's incursion into Russia's Kursk region.

item.title: Delta plane tire explosion: Tragedy at maintenance facility leaves workers dead, investigation under way
item.description: A pre-dawn explosion erupted at Delta Air Lines' maintenance facility at Atlanta's Hartsfield-Jackson airport, claiming the lives of two workers and injuring a third. Occurring in the wheel and brake shop, the cause is yet to be determined. The incident did not disrupt airport operations, and investigations are underway.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Northwestern University faces criticism over removal of Arab students' photos
item.description: Northwestern University’s medical school reportedly removed photos of Arab students wearing keffiyehs from social media, sparking a demand for a public apology and investigation by the Students for Justice in Palestine. The university cites student safety as the reason for the deletion. This incident follows earlier episodes of violence and discrimination against Palestinian students in educational settings.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US Army private who escaped to North Korea will plead guilty to desertion
item.description: US Army private Travis King, who entered North Korea last year and was detained, plans to plead guilty to five charges, including desertion. He faces a total of 14 charges but will have nine dismissed as part of a plea agreement. ​​​King, who joined the Army in 2021, was previously detained in South Korea for assault. His sentencing is scheduled for September 20 at Fort Bliss, Texas.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Ride hailing works even if...': Elon Musk jokes as SpaceX will rescue Nasa astronauts
item.description: John Hanna joked that SpaceX had started a ride-hailing service by aiding NASA with returning astronauts from the ISS. Elon Musk responded by hinting at a Tesla-SpaceX collaboration. Due to technical issues, astronauts Butch Wilmore and Sunita Williams will stay longer on the ISS, returning no earlier than next September.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump mocked for launching bizarre NFT cards featuring him dancing: 'Imagine voting for this fraudster'
item.description: ​Donald Trump Tuesday announced the launch of a fresh batch of digital trading cards where Trump will be seen dancing, posing as a "sneakerhead" wearing his own line of golden shoes, clad in an Iron Man-like suit etc. The fundraising push comes as Harris-Walz merch have been an instant hit in the market. Trump announced the launch of the America First collection featuring 50 images. The cards cost $99 each.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump says he's reached agreement with Kamala Harris for Sept 10 debate. Rules are...
item.description: ​ After much dillydally over debate, Donald Trump Tuesday announced he had agreed with the Kamala Harris camp for the September 10 debate on ABC news -- the first debate between the two after Joe Biden pulled out of the presidential race following his CNN debate debacle. Trump and Kamala camps had been warring over the debate rules for quite some time. In his social media post, Trump announced that the debate rules will be same as the last CNN debate.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
